<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
i3ullseye recently started threads dealing with each of our spell-lines specifically.  I am going to post a response to each thread containing my thoughts about each of the spell lines, but I feel it would be more useful for me to deal with the "whole picture" first before breaking it down and getting into the specifics. That having been said, lets take a look at the very interesting (and frankly absurd) breakdown of our debuff lines…<P>Body Twisting:<BR>Strength Debuff<P>Disorientation (Body Spec Line):<BR>AoE Dexterity / Quickness Debuff<BR>Heat Resistance Debuff<P>Matter Twisting:<BR>Dexterity Debuff<P>Telekinesis (Matter Spec Line):<BR>AoE Dexterity / Quickness Debuff<P>Mind Twisting:<BR>(none)<P>Domination (Mind Spec Line):<BR>Strength / Constitution Debuff<P>This makes absolutely no sense to me.  Not sure about everyone else, but I propose the following changes take place.  First, move the Str/Con debuff from the mind spec line to the body spec line replacing the AoE dex/qui debuff.  This would give the str debuff in the body base line with the dual str/con debuff in the spec line.  A much more logical scenario.  That would then leave the dex debuff in the matter base line with the dual dex/qui debuff in the spec line.  Again, a much more logical scenario and it eliminates the ridiculous redundancy involved with having the same dual debuff in both spec lines.  I would then encourage the developers to come up with some sort of replacement line for Domination that would make sense.  They could even move the heat resistance debuff to the domination spec line with the justification being the sorcerer instills in the target a deep aversion to heat.  They would then have to come up with some other type of resistance for our cabalist brothers for their class specific spec so that they do not lose anything.  The resulting setup would look like the following…<P>Body Twisting:<BR>Strength Debuff<P>Disorientation (Body Spec Line):<BR>Strength / Constitution Debuff<P><BR>Matter Twisting:<BR>Dexterity Debuff<P>Telekinesis (Matter Spec Line):<BR>AoE Dexterity / Quickness Debuff<P>Mind Twisting:<BR>(none)<P>Domination (Mind Spec Line):<BR>Heat Resistance Debuff<P>This makes a great deal more sense in my opinion and serves to differentiate a sorcerer spec'ing in Body as opposed to someone spec'ing in Matter.<P>--------------------<P>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>Dyzmond the Avalonian Sorcerer<BR>Member of the Furious Pantaloons<BR>Galahad Server<BR>Member of the Sorcerer Testing Team in Beta<BR>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<P>"Who could ever calculate the path of a molecule?<BR>How do we know that the creations of worlds are not determined by falling grains of sand?"<BR>  --Victor Hugo, Les Miserables
</FONT>
