<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well, okay, Captain, I am going to take a stab at speaking to your concerns because I believe there is a valid point at the heart of what your saying...<P>Let me start by saying that it has long been understood that the life of a primarily mind-specced sorcerer is the toughest of all three branches in terms of RvR.  Many of the spells that are invaluable in PvE have little if any effect in RvR.  So your contention that the, "line has a lot of utilities but thats all" is valid provided that we are speaking in terms of RvR.  <P>If we were speaking in terms of PvE, then the story would be somewhat different.  The primarily mind specced sorcerer would have a number of weapons in his arsenal.  In PvE, a mind specced sorcerer would give a body specced sorcerer a run for his money and certainly would be the more desirable of the two in many group situations.  It is in this spirit that I believe i3ullseye made his comment about the mind school seeming, "...pretty meaty".<P>So in light of all this, I would tend to agree with both of you on one level or another.  But I really started out wanting to address your concerns over the suggested re-organization of the debuffs, so let me stop rambling and get right to it.<P>Lets take your hypothetical RvR scenario...<P>"So I meet a troll in the middle of nowhere I AE Mez him, send in pet, then what?"<P>Well, if my limited experience in RvR is any indication (and I fully invite those that have done extensive RvR to weigh in on this subject) the troll will ignore your pet and make a straight line for your head with his huge hammer the moment your pet breaks the mez.  So lets assume at some point in all this, either before, during or after the mez, you cast your dual str/con debuff.  So, okay, now you have reduced his strenght which will effect his damage output, and reduced his con which will effect his hit points.  But what difference does this really make in the bigger picture? You have done no direct damage to him other than what your pet has been able to do in the time it took him to run up to you.  <P>I believe at the heart of what your saying, captain, is a recognition of a fundamental imbalance in the usefulness of the mind school in terms of RvR when compared to PvE.  And on that level I agree.  In beta we spent countless lines coming up with ideas to implement spells like confusion in a way such that it would be useful, to no avail.  The bottom line, in my opinion, is that this line's usefulness, or lack thereof, has little to do with whether or not the Str/Con debuff is in it.<P>So I re-affirm my contention that the debuff lines in particular make absolutely no sense the way they are currently distributed.  Re-aligning them in the way I propose would at least give some believable in-character justification for having the dual debuffs in the spec lines of the schools where the single debuff is contained in the base.<P>Just my thoughts....<P>--------------------<P>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>Dyzmond the Avalonian Sorcerer<BR>Member of the Furious Pantaloons<BR>Galahad Server<BR>Member of the Sorcerer Testing Team in Beta<BR>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<P>"Who could ever calculate the path of a molecule?<BR>How do we know that the creations of worlds are not determined by falling grains of sand?"<BR>  --Victor Hugo, Les Miserables
